data.title: Verbund Casimcea Wind Farm
data.text: The Verbund Casimcea Wind Farm is an operational wind power project located in Tulcea County, Romania. It consists of 88 individual wind turbines with a nominal output 2.5 MW each which will deliver up to 540 GWh of power, enough to power over 350,000 homes, with a capital investment required of approximately â¬380 million.[1]
